---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Work | Amid the Noise">
  <section class="section" data-pagefind-ignore>
    <article>
      <h1>Work</h1>
      <p class="work-operator">
        I design decision systems that make ambiguous signals legible, governable, and actionable under pressure.
      </p>
      <p class="work-intro">
        Selected case studies across AI, enterprise systems, automation, and regulated environments, focused on problem framing, decision clarity, constraints, and outcomes.
      </p>

      <div class="decision-grid" aria-label="Work section overview">
        <a class="decision-card" href="#recent-work">
          <span>Recent Work</span>
          <p>Enterprise systems, decisions, and outcomes.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="decision-card" href="#foundations">
          <span>Foundations</span>
          <p>Early product and platform patterns.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="decision-card" href="#current-work">
          <span>Current Work</span>
          <p>Advisory, civic systems, and applied research.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section work-list" data-pagefind-ignore>
    <h2 id="recent-work">Recent Work</h2>

    <article class="work-entry">
      <h3>Dremio</h3>
      <p class="work-meta">Principal Product Designer · 2021–2022</p>
      <p>Designing decision clarity in distributed data systems used by enterprise data teams.</p>
      <p><a href="/work/dremio">Read case study →</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="work-entry">
      <h3>Automation Anywhere</h3>
      <p class="work-meta">Principal Product Designer · 2019–2021</p>
      <p>Designing decision control in AI automation systems managing enterprise workflows.</p>
      <p><a href="/work/automation-anywhere">Read case study →</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="work-entry">
      <h3>Wells Fargo</h3>
      <p class="work-meta">Lead Product Designer · 2019</p>
      <p>Designing decision governance in regulated AI systems within financial services.</p>
      <p><a href="/work/wells-fargo">Read case study →</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="work-entry">
      <h3>CA Technologies</h3>
      <p class="work-meta">Principal Product Designer · Incubator · 2016–2019</p>
      <p>Designing early-stage enterprise systems from exploration to scale.</p>
      <p><a href="/work/ca-technologies">Read case study →</a></p>
    </article>

    <aside class="work-learning-note" aria-label="Related field studies">
      <p>
        For deeper operational analysis, see <a href="/learning">Learning</a>, where field studies examine governance, AI decision workflows, and complex systems in greater detail.
      </p>

      <p class="work-learning-link">
        <a href="/learning">Browse Field Studies →</a>
      </p>
    </aside>

    <h2 id="foundations">Foundations</h2>

    <article class="work-entry">
      <h3>Autodesk</h3>
      <p class="work-meta">Enterprise Licensing Platform (Autodesk Account) · 2012</p>
      <p>Aligning fragmented legacy systems, stakeholder ownership, and cloud licensing workflows without formal authority.</p>
      <p><a href="/writing/designing-under-constraint-autodesk">Read case study →</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="work-entry">
      <h3>Designing Systems Before They Were Called Systems</h3>
      <p>Early lessons from Friendster, Autodesk, and Evernote on how systems can appear to function while failing beneath the surface.</p>
      <p><a href="/work/designing-systems-before-they-were-called-systems">Read case study →</a></p>
    </article>

    <h2 id="current-work">Current Work</h2>

    <article class="work-entry">
      <h3>Amid the Noise</h3>
      <p>
        Advising on AI, decision systems, and governance across enterprise and civic domains, including financial institutions and national security policy contexts.
      </p>
      <p>
        This work extends into writing and analysis, applying system-level thinking from software to civic infrastructure, public trust, and institutional decision-making.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="work-entry">
      <h3>Designing Decision Systems Under Uncertainty</h3>
      <p>Designing decision clarity in ambiguous environments by surfacing boundaries, aligning stakeholders, and making complex systems actionable.</p>
      <p><a href="/work/designing-decision-systems-under-uncertainty">Read case study →</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="work-entry">
      <h3>HARMONIC and the Patent Cluster</h3>
      <p class="work-meta">Author · 2025–2026</p>
      <p>Designing a system layer that makes probabilistic AI outputs usable in real decisions by exposing confidence, surfacing uncertainty, and defining when human judgment must intervene.</p>
      <p>Applies the HARMONIC framework to bridge model behavior and operator judgment in high-stakes environments, with a focus on escalation logic, trust calibration, and decision accountability.</p>
      <p><a href="/work/harmonic-framework">Read case study →</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="work-entry">
      <h3>Santa Clara County Registrar of Voters</h3>
      <p class="work-meta">Vote Center Manager · 2026</p>
      <p>Designing access and observability in civic decision systems at county scale.</p>
      <p><a href="/work/santa-clara-county-registrar-of-voters">Read case study →</a></p>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .work-operator {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .work-intro {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .work-learning-note {
    max-width: 46rem;
    margin: 1.1rem 0 0.75rem;
    padding: 1rem 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    color: var(--secondary);
  }

  .work-learning-note p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .work-learning-link {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .work-learning-link a {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--text);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .work-learning-link a:hover,
  .work-learning-link a:focus-visible {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 0.14em;
  }

  .work-learning-note a {
    color: var(--text);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .work-learning-note a:hover,
  .work-learning-note a:focus-visible {
    border-bottom-color: var(--text);
  }

  .decision-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 14px;
    margin-top: 34px;
    max-width: 56rem;
  }

  .decision-card {
    display: block;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding: 18px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .decision-card:hover,
  .decision-card:focus-visible {
    border-color: var(--text);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .decision-card span {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .decision-card p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .decision-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .work-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .work-entry {
    padding: 1.1rem 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .work-meta {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--secondary, #64748b);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .work-entry h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .work-entry p {
    margin: 0.3rem 0;
  }

  .work-list h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color, #e5e7eb);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .work-list h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }
</style>